Altran Chief Fights Apax Efforts to Oust Him, La Tribune Says

-- B y   M a r t h e   F o u r c a d e
-- 
2011-05-17T06:36:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/altran-chief-fights-apax-efforts-to-oust-him-la-tribune-says.html
Altran Technologies SA (ALT)  Chief
Executive Officer Yves de Chaisemartin is fighting efforts by
Apax Partners LLP to oust him at next month’s annual meeting,  La
Tribune  reported, without saying where it got the information.  Chaisemartin says Apax, which owns 19.2 percent of the
company’s shares and 31.2 percent of the votes, is trying to use
double  voting rights , according to the French newspaper.
Chaisemartin is also proposing three new board members to
counter Apax’s plan to name two new candidates, La Tribune said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marthe Fourcade in Paris at 
 mfourcade@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root in Paris at 
 vroot@bloomberg.net . 